g!gaplog                    Creates a log (ADMIN USE ONLY [*note - perms are not pre-set to your administrators.*])

g!freezechannel             Removes ability for users to chat in the channel that the command is used.
g!unfreezechannel           Restores ability for users to chat in the channel that the command is used.

actions.message:
To be fair, you have to have a very high IQ to understand Jojo's Bizarre Adventure. The action is extremely subtle, and without a solid grasp of music history most of the stands will go over a typical reader's head. There‚Äôs also Joseph's nihilistic outlook, which is deftly woven into his characterisation- his personal philosophy draws heavily from his old friend, Ceasar Zeppeli; for instance. The fans understand this stuff; they have the intellectual capacity to truly appreciate the depths of these characters, to realise that they‚Äôre not just intelligent- they say something deep about LIFE. As a consequence people who dislike Jojo truly ARE idiots- of course they wouldn‚Äôt appreciate, for instance, the history in Jotaro‚Äôs existential catchphrase ‚Äúyare yare daze‚Äù which itself is a cryptic reference to the classic comic 'peanuts' and Charlie Brown's character. I‚Äôm smirking right now just imagining one of those addlepated simpletons scratching their heads in confusion as Araki's genius wit unfolds itself on their pages. What fools.. how I pity them. :joy_cat::joy_cat::joy_cat:

And yes, by the way, i DO have a Joestar birthmark tattoo. And no, you cannot see it. It‚Äôs for the duwangs‚Äô eyes only- and even then they have to demonstrate that they‚Äôre within 5 IQ points of my own (preferably lower) beforehand.
